    {
      "id": 7,
      "title": "Global vs Regional Metrics Explanation",
      "type": "text",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 22
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**Note on Global vs Regional Metrics:**\n\n- **Global Metrics**: Some sub-indices (e.g., economic_stress, mobility_activity, digital_attention) are computed from national/global data sources and may show identical values across regions. This is expected behavior.\n- **Regional Metrics**: Other sub-indices (e.g., environmental_stress, political_stress) are computed from region-specific data and will differ between regions.\n- **Behavior Index**: The overall behavior index combines both global and regional components using weighted aggregation, so regional differences reflect regional-specific factors even when some components are identical."
      }
